During this project, one of the main challenges I faced was understanding how to connect JavaScript to the HTML and update the DOM correctly. I worked through this by creating functions to re-render the task list each time changes were made, which helped ensure the display stayed up to date.

Another challenge was working with arrays and objects together, especially when storing and updating task data. I approached this by breaking the problem into smaller steps and focusing on how each part of the code contributed to the overall functionality.

I also explored using local storage, even though it was not required, so that tasks would remain saved after refreshing the page. This gave me a better understanding of how data can persist in a web application.

If I had more time, I would go back to the beginning of the class and review everything again at a slower pace so I can fully understand each concept.
